{"id": "EUVD-2018-8670", "enisaUuid": "05a0574c-2e47-353a-b724-6bb01d73d505", "description": "A flaw was found in the Linux kernel's handle_rx() function in the [vhost_net] driver. A malicious virtual guest, under specific conditions, can trigger an out-of-bounds write in a kmalloc-8 slab on a virtual host which may lead to a kernel memory corruption and a system panic. Due to the nature of the flaw, privilege escalation cannot be fully ruled out. Versions from v4.16 and newer are vulnerable.", "datePublished": "2019-01-29T16:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T10:32:54", "baseScore": 5.9, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:A/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:L/A:N", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-16880.html", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-16880", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3903-2/", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=CVE-2018-16880", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/106735", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/3903-1/", "https://support.f5.com/csp/article/K03593314", "http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-05/msg00037.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-16880"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.1, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "a5f23b44-b7f0-3ded-b931-4b6e259e6ebb", "product": {"name": "Kernel"}, "product_version": "from v4.16 and newer"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "0e55d809-ffe7-373f-bc1d-beb14c04b73b", "vendor": {"name": "The Linux Foundation"}}], "isExploited": false}